  "instructions": [
    "combine brown lentils and 1 cup of water in a medium saucepan, bring to a boil and then simmer for 20 minutes.",
    "in a small bowl, mix together onion, garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "heat 1 tbsp of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat, add the spice mixture and cook for 1 minute.",
    "add the labneh cheese to the skillet and stir until melted, then set aside.",
    "heat the remaining 1 tbsp of olive oil in a separate skillet over medium heat.",
    "add the lentils to the skillet and cook for 2-3 minutes, breaking them up with a spoon as they cook.",
    "stir in the chopped parsley and lemon juice, then serve the lentils in a bowl and top with the labneh cheese mixture.",
    "grill the mixture over robata-grill for 2-3 minutes, or until lightly browned and crispy.",
    "serve hot and enjoy!"
  ],
